LAGOS – As the prestigious Ibadan Golf Club (IGC) is set to commission its multi-purpose administrative building which was donated to them by a member, Barr Abiodun Olatunji, captain of the club, Tunji Oladosu, has commended the late captain of the club, Ola Ibironke, vowing to sustain his legacy. Oladosu said this while addressing press ahead of the program lined up for the commissioning scheduled for May 11 to 14, 2022, saying the project was initiated by the late Ibironke popularly known as ‘Dudu Heritage’ regretting that it was quite unfortunate that he was no more to witness the commissioning. “We are assuring you that we are keeping the good works that he has started and that is why we are going to honour him with this project; the VIP lounge will be named after him as a way of immortalizing his good name and the numerous good work he had done for this great club,” said Oladosu. -Advertisement- He added: “The structure could be ranked among the best in the golf clubs in Nigeria with top notch facilities such as modernized bar which is of international standard and a well equipped VIP lounge, while we also now have a pro-shop whereby golfers materials will be displayed for sale.” Also speaking during the press briefing, chairman of the building committee, Yomi Salami, said over 250 golfers were expected to participate in the golf competition designed as activities to mark the commissioning with Governor Seyi Makinde, who is also a member of the club, expecting to cut the tape to commission the block.